<?xml version="1.0"?>
<html>
  <problem>
    <title>CheckPoint: Force and Simple Harmonic Motion</title>
        <p>Which of the following equations describes simple harmonic motion? <b>Check all that apply.</b> Note that F, x, v, and a stand for, respectively, force, position, velocity, and acceleration. Symbol c is a positive constant.</p>


  <choiceresponse>
    <checkboxgroup direction="vertical">
      <choice correct="false"><text>\(F=-cv\)</text></choice>
      <choice correct="false"><text>\(F=-ca\)</text></choice>
      <choice correct="true"><text>\(F=-cx\)</text></choice>
      <choice correct="false"><text>\(F=+cx\)</text></choice>
      <choice correct="false"><text>\(F=+cv\)</text></choice>
      <choice correct="false"><text>\(F=+ca\)</text></choice>
      <choice correct="true"><text>\(F=-x/c\)</text></choice>
      <choice correct="false"><text>\(F=-x^2/c\)</text></choice>
      <choice correct="false"><text>\(F=-cv^2\)</text></choice>
    </checkboxgroup>
  </choiceresponse>


  </problem>
</html>
